I don't know why I picked Cotton Candy.  Chocolate is objectively better as well as many other flavors.   Either way, it represented the cherry on the sundae of happiness during a time where I was considering self harm.  That is why Kawartha Dairy ice cream is so special to me.

This camp was for 6 weeks, away from family, and it was up in the Halliburton region in Northern Ontario.  Every Sunday we would take a trip into the city to go swimming and get ice cream.  Every other Sunday we went to the Kawartha Dairy to get our ice cream.

But because of my learning disabilities and social issues, I was able to attend a summer camp specifically designed for people with these kinds of issues.  I was able to go two years in a row, the second being special because I was over the age limit.
All of this lead to behavior issues and thoughts that were dark.  Normally my summers wouldn't be that much better.

Because I always got along better with others with disabilities, I found it harder to get on with the normal kids.  I also had problems in Phys-Ed with an overbearing teacher and I couldn't keep up with other students.

1992 and 1993 were both some of the worst years of my life, and the best.  I was in a school where I was bulled, not just by other students, but teachers as well.  Having Learning Disabilities, I was intergreted into regular classrooms instead of in the LD classroom.
Well since Kawartha Dairy is tending, let me tell you about why my favorite flavor of ice cream is Cotton Candy.
